---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in XI — Unusual X-Ending Plays" description="Learn the valid Scrabble words ending in XI including TAXI, MAXI, and more. These rare X-ending words score big on premium squares." keywords="words ending in xi, scrabble xi words, taxi scrabble, maxi scrabble, x ending words scrabble, xi ending words">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Ending in XI — Unusual X-Ending Plays",
    "description": "Learn the valid Scrabble words ending in XI for high-scoring X plays.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-22",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }
  })}></script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words end in XI in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The main Scrabble words ending in XI are TAXI (11pts) and MAXI (13pts). In SOWPODS dictionaries, PIXI (13pts) is also valid. This is one of the rarest word endings in the game." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is TAXI a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. TAXI is valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS dictionaries. It scores 11 points and can be extended to TAXIS (12pts) or TAXIED (14pts)." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many XI-ending words exist in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Very few — TAXI and MAXI are the primary ones in TWL. SOWPODS adds PIXI and a handful of others. XI-endings are among the rarest in Scrabble, making them valuable surprise plays." }}
    ]
  })}></script>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-white">← Blog</a> <span class="mx-2">›</span> <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in XI</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-8">Updated June 22, 2026 · 3 min read</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">Words ending in XI are among the rarest in the Scrabble dictionary. While the list is short, these words pack a punch — the X tile alone is worth 8 points, and placing it on a premium square can swing the game.</p>

      <div class="border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10 rounded-xl p-6 mb-10 grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-center">
        <div><span class="text-amber-400 text-2xl font-bold">3</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Valid XI words</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-amber-400 text-2xl font-bold">13pts</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Top scorer (MAXI)</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-amber-400 text-2xl font-bold">8pts</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">X tile value alone</span></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Complete XI-Ending Word List</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
        <table class="w-full border border-gray-700 rounded-lg text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800"><tr><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Word</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Points</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Dictionary</th><th class="p-3 text-left text-gray-300">Extensions</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="p-3 text-white font-bold">TAXI</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">TWL + SOWPODS</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">TAXIS, TAXIED, TAXIING</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="p-3 text-white font-bold">MAXI</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">TWL + SOWPODS</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">MAXIS, MAXIM</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="p-3 text-white font-bold">PIXI</td><td class="p-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-300">SOWPODS only</td><td class="p-3 text-gray-400">PIXIE, PIXIES</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold mb-2">Quick Insight</p>
        <p class="text-gray-300">XI itself is a valid 2-letter word (the Greek letter) worth 9 points. It's one of the highest-scoring 2-letter words in Scrabble and can be used as a hook to form TAXI or MAXI from existing board letters.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for XI Words</h2>

      <div class="border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold mb-2">Strategy Tips</p>
        <ul class="text-gray-300 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Hook XI onto T or M:</span> If the board has a T or M in a good spot, extend it to TAXI or MAXI for instant 11-13 points.</li>
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Double Letter on X:</span> Placing X on a DLS square doubles it to 16 points, making TAXI worth 19 and MAXI worth 21.</li>
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Parallel plays:</span> TAXI and MAXI are short enough to play parallel to existing words, forming multiple 2-letter combinations.</li>
          <li><span class="text-purple-400 font-bold">Extend later:</span> TAXI becomes TAXIS (12pts) or TAXIED (14pts) — keep the spot open for a future turn.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Other X-Ending Patterns</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">If XI endings don't fit your rack, consider these other X-ending patterns:</p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-10">
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">WAX</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOX</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOX</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">HEX</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">MIX</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg px-3 py-2"><span class="text-white font-bold">JINX</span> <span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-indigo-400 font-semibold mb-2">Related Reads</p>
        <ul class="text-gray-300 space-y-1">
          <li><a href="/blog/words-ending-in-ex" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Words Ending in EX</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/words-ending-in-ax" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Words Ending in AX</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/words-with-x-in-the-middle" class="text-indigo-400 hover:underline">Words With X in the Middle</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl p-6 text-center mb-10">
        <p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Find X Words For Your Rack</p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Enter your tiles and our solver finds every X-word placement — including XI-endings.</p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition">Try the Word Finder →</a>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-8 mt-12">
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-4">Related Articles</p>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-ex" class="block border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-4 transition"><span class="text-white">Words Ending in EX</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">REX, VEX, HEX and more X-enders</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-in-ax" class="block border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 rounded-lg p-4 transition"><span class="text-white">Words Ending in AX</span><br><span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">WAX, TAX, MAX — classic scoring plays</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="mt-8"><a href="/blog" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-white text-sm">← Back to Blog</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
